Follow-up draft instruction:
- The follow-up `description` is what users edit before the future toast is created.
- Write `description` as complete free text describing exactly what must be done.
- If the decision notes mention named accounts, documents, markets, owners, processes, proof points, dates, or dependencies, include the relevant ones directly in `description`.
- Keep `title` short; it is only a temporary label before the Toast draft refinement flow creates the final title and description.
- `reason` may explain why the follow-up exists, but it must not be the only place where the concrete execution context appears.

